name: 多米尼克·诺斯
name_full: 多米尼克·诺斯 Dominic North
introduction: Dominic Andrew North Born 1983 Leeds, England, is an English ballet dancer. UK Occupation Dancer.Joined New Adventures: 2004Dominic has been a principal dancer with New Adventures since 2008 with roles including the Prince in Swan Lake; Julian and Ivan in The Red Shoes, Angelo in The Car Man, Edward in EdwardScissorhands, Cyril Vane in Dorian Gray, Ralph in Lord of the Flies, Early Adventures, Fritz in Nutcracker!, Leo in Sleeping Beauty and Harry the Pilot in Cinderella. Dominic has also performed in Swan Lake 3D, Matthew Bourne’s Christmas, and the film versions of Sleeping Beauty and The Car Man.Dominic has been a dance captain on many productions and has been a workshop leader for New Adventures since 2008 and a Resident Artist since 2012.
